Description: Papyrus written with black ink with demotic legal text on recto (9 ll.), verso blank. Thompson's MS Catalogue: "Official receipt for grain received as the rent of town land (?) Date year 10 Payni 7 [of Ptolemy Philometor] = BC. 171 July 9". Nos. 10575-10601 from the Siut Archive.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (45565) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/45565)
Acquisition notes: Purchased from M. Nahman. Cf. the additional sheets at the end of Thompson's MS Catalogue, titled "B.M. Nahman Papyri (1923)".
